"{\"content\":{\"body\":\"Galaxy Digital, a cryptocurrency brokerage and merchant bank founded by billionaire investor Michael Novogratz, [announced](https://www.newswire.ca/news-releases/galaxy-digital-announces-pricing-of-500-million-exchangeable-senior-notes-offering-895416527.html) on Monday that it would be issuing $500 million in exchangeable senior notes to accelerate business initiatives. The debt is convertible into company equity and bears an interest rate of 3% per annum, with maturity in 2026. New expansion areas include nonfungible tokens, or NFTs, with the firm [committing](https://www.newswire.ca/news-releases/galaxy-digital-announces-third-quarter-2021-financial-results-896789456.html#:\\\\~:text=Galaxy%20Digital%20Asset%20Management%20(%22GDAM,in%20the%20Galaxy%20Interactive%20funds.) $62 million of its capital into 22 NFT-related companies since the start of the year.\\n\\nOver the years, Galaxy Digital founder and CEO Mike Novogratz has been a [famed bullish investor](https://cointelegraph.com/top-people-in-crypto-and-blockchain-2021/mike-novogratz) of Bitcoin ([BTC](https://cointelegraph.com/bitcoin-price)) and other cryptocurrencies. He has called on other investors to allocate anywhere between 1% to 5% of their portfolio to crypto. Under his guidance, the firm's assets under management surpassed $3 billion in an update provided in October, becoming one of the largest digital currency investment companies in the world.\",\"timestamp\":1639119826,\"title\":\"Galaxy Digital raises $500 million in\"},\"digest\":\"OxWTTEDrPXowrWRkbiDoqFgXyOKx5rLTQ2fZd66fBTM\",\"authorship\":{\"contributor\":\"0x4CC063B69212E7662449e32738A2b47508e93AcB\",\"signingKey\":\"{\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\\\"ext\\\":true,\\\"key_ops\\\":[\\\"verify\\\"],\\\"kty\\\":\\\"EC\\\",\\\"x\\\":\\\"uWMX-7kXToQSD7kJv5HVlo-UViAo3twKqOVwOoppiGA\\\",\\\"y\\\":\\\"3V5DwVD70jbmsEycBBiMsUJbNHKuIZPMknQV1hK_-js\\\"}\",\"signature\":\"KoR6x69kRZRWm-o_jYL3HNs5GrwSfkSi4TqVYe3pdwoqLv3Se6P4OH9fY0